data: Blackburn's Rivers Important to Lancashire Landscape Investment And Natural Capital Economy (BRILLIaNCE)
Improving the biodiversity of two rivers in Lancashire through the creation of a natural river bed and introdution of fish passes to allow fish to access the river upstream

Aligns 2010 Lawton report Making Space for Nature, 2011 Nat Env paper ‘Natural Choice’,one of four drivers identified by Ecosystems Task Force (2013).Aligns England Biodiversity Strategy 2020& Defra appraisal scored the vfm as satisfactory.
